div.h3: Introducing “Statistics for Strava”: An Open-Source app that analyses your Strava data
div.p: Strava is a fantastic tool for tracking your workouts, but its built-in analytics may not always provide the depth of insight data enthusiasts seek. Enter Statistics for Strava, an open-source, self-hosted web application that provides you with alternative stats and fun insights.

div.h3: Transform Your Raspberry Pi into a Digital Photo Frame
div.p: The Raspberry Pi is an affordable, compact device that can easily turn a monitor into a customisable digital photo frame, displaying your favorite photos in a continuous slideshow. I’ll be using Immich, a self-hosted photo and video management solution, to achieve this.

div.h3: I created a public API that exposes WCA competition results
div.p: The World Cube Association governs competitions for mechanical puzzles that are operated by twisting groups of pieces, commonly known as ‘twisty puzzles’.

div.h3: How I got to solving the Rubik’s cube in under 30 seconds
div.p: About six months ago I wrote a blog post about how I got to solving the Rubik’s cube in under 60 seconds consistently. Since then, I have been working on improving and getting even faster solves.
